		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Berlin Marquette County Wisconsin</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>October 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>Rev Sir</p>
				<p rend="indent(1)">You will undoubtedly be pleased<lb/> to hear&#44; that in this <placeName>Backwood Country</placeName><lb/> there <sic>where</sic> assembled on the Day of atone&#45;<lb/>ment a few of our people to praise the Lord<lb/> on high.  We meet to the number of thirteen<lb/> at the house of <persName>Mr Kensel</persName>&#44; who lives about<lb/> twenty miles north of this Place&#44; on Lands<lb/> belonging to the late <sic>menomienee</sic> purchase<lb/> so you will&#44; that the Land are not even<lb/> sold yet to actual settlers&#44; and yet in that wilder&#95;<lb/>ness where a few of Gods <sic>choosen</sic> ones assembled<lb/> to sing praises to his name.  We had everything<lb/> to make the Day pass off&#44; according to ancient usage<lb/>  There was <add>Hebrew</add> and <add>Hebrew</add> belonging to <persName>Mr Kusel</persName><lb/> and there was also in our small congregation a<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> and a <add>Hebrew</add> and everything went off to the satis&#61;<lb/>faction of every body present.  Knowing that you<lb/> take a great <sic>intress</sic> in everything concerning<lb/> our holy faith&#44; I send you this Lines thinking<lb/> that <sic>the</sic> will be read by you with pleasure</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>and if you should see fit to publish the<lb/> same in the next number of the Occi&#45;<lb/>dent&#44; you will oblige very much your<lb/> most obd. Servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">M. Markwell</persName></p>
		</body>
